ivate my spell, sending white hot, super heated bolt of fire at it. Hitting it squarely in the chest, my bolt of fire lifted it up and throw it away from me, dead before it even hit the ground.<br>
<br>
Looking around, I quickly picked my next opponent. Again holding my book, I began casting again, only to find that there was a closer one who took it upon itself to swing at me. Trusting in my own defensive spells to take the brunt of the attack, I continued casting. A dull ache spread from my back as the things club struck home, but thankfully doing little damage to me through my armor or spells. My bolt, however, did so much more. Firing from my eyes this time, leaving white spots in my vision, I watched as it sped towards the far creature, entering its body just below the rib cage. It stopped and yelped as an orangie glow eminated from it's own eyes. A look of pure surprise flashed across its face before being replaced by a look of utter pain. Opening its mouth to scream, instead let out a stream of fire that shoot into the sky. In a fiery blast that shortly followed, its body disintegrated into a pile of ash.<br>
<br>
